stages.question:
Sam plans to invite all his friends over to his house for a party night, he finds his house quite bland for a party and wants to change his walls to blue.
 First select the class of the wall using .walls{} and use the 'background-color' styling.
Example: .element {background-color: color}

stages.original_css:
.house {width: 200px;height: 200px; 
 position: relative;} 
 .roof {width: 0;height: 0;border-left: 100px solid transparent;border-right: 100px solid transparent;border-bottom: 60px solid #d9534f; position: absolute;top: 0;} 
 .walls {width: 100%;height: 140px;background-color: pink ;position: absolute;bottom: 0;} 
 .door {width: 40px;height: 80px;background-color: #704214; position: absolute;bottom: 10px;left: 50%;transform: translateX(-50%);} 
 .window {width: 40px;height: 40px;background-color: #aad5e7; 
 position: absolute;top: 50px; margin-left:8px; margin-right:8px;} 
 .window:first-child {left: 30px;} 
 .window:last-child {right: 0px;}

